/bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy can disprove tautologies.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy's programs always terminate -- sometimes each  other.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy's programs don't need a garbage collector;  they pick up their OWN garbage. </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy doesn't make system calls. System calls call  Doug McIlroy. </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy doesn't use malloc to allocate memory.  He  uses his bare hands.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy doesn't debug. He stares at tty0 until it  fixes the problem.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Once, Doug McIlroy got mad at his terminal and smacked the  keyboard.  The result is called "Unix."  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Alan Turing always wanted to win a McIlroy Award, but  didn't qualify.  No one has.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>In 1984, the Department of Justice broke up AT&amp;T because they had a monopoly. On Doug McIlroy.  </bod1>  <p><bod1>Doug McIlroy supervises the hypervisor.  </bod1>    <td align="left" valign="top"> </td>                             </table></div></body></html>